0Educate%20Girls%2C%20an%20NGO%20that%20is%20attempting%20to%20ensure%20that%20every%20girl%20and%20woman%20gets%20access%20to%20education%20%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDue%20to%20personal%20circumstances%2C%20Safeena%20stopped%20going%20to%20school.%20She%20watched%20her%20friends%20breeze%20through%20higher%20classes%20and%20college.%20She%20points%20out%2C%20%E2%80%9CIn%20times%20like%20these%2C%20you%20can%20feel%20your%20confidence%20and%20self-esteem%20fall.%20You%20think%20you%20don%E2%80%99t%20deserve%20anything%20in%20life.%20No%20girl%20should%20have%20to%20go%20through%20it.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20they%20do.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%204.1%20million%20girls%20went%20through%20it%20between%202020%20and%202022%2C%20according%20to%20a%20report%20by%20UDISE%2B%20(Unified%20District%20Information%20System%20for%20Education%20Plus)%2C%20a%20management%20information%20system%20of%20the%20Department%20of%20School%20Education%20and%20Literacy%2C%20Union%20Ministry%20of%20Education.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENot%20just%20in%20India%2C%20but%20across%20the%20world%2C%20history%20bears%20witness%20to%20girls%20being%20consigned%20to%20the%20waiting%20room%20of%20education%2C%20hoping%20their%20names%20will%20be%20called%2C%20hoping%20for%20a%20chance%20to%20study.%20In%20Safeena%E2%80%99s%20case%2C%20it%20was%20an%20aunt%20who%20helped%20her%20navigate%20the%20metaphorical%20waiting%20room%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F469615%2Fdhir-jhingran-ex-ias-officer-assam-kokrajhar-started-language-and-learning-foundation-primary-school-teaching-methods%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecoaxing%20her%20to%20get%20back%20to%20academics%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20offering%20her%20all%20the%20guidance%20needed.%20And%20once%20she%20did%2C%20Safeena%20says%2C%20things%20dramatically%20changed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20world%20began%20to%20look%20at%20me%20very%20differently.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EFrom%20privilege%20to%20promise%3A%20Flipping%20the%20notion%20of%20girl%20child%20education%20in%20India%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CClose%20your%20eyes%2C%E2%80%9D%20Safeena%20encourages%20me.%20%E2%80%9CImagine%20an%20out-of-school%20girl%20and%20what%20her%20life%20looks%20like.%20She%20gets%20up%20in%20the%20morning%2C%20she%20cooks%2C%20she%20cleans%2C%20she%20grazes%20the%20goats%2C%20she%20takes%20the%20cattle%20out%2C%20feeds%20them%2C%20does%20more%20cooking%2C%20more%20cleaning%2C%20and%20then%20she%20goes%20to%20bed.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20picture%20gives%20me%20goosebumps.%20Safeena%20senses%20my%20discomfort.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-quote%20wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNow%20close%20your%20eyes%20again%20and%20imagine%20a%20girl%20who%20goes%20to%20school.%20She%20gets%20up%20in%20the%20morning%2C%20she%20puts%20on%20her%20uniform%2C%20has%20breakfast%2C%20walks%20to%20school%2C%20studies%2C%20plays%20with%20her%20friends%3B%20there%20are%20doors%20of%20opportunity%20waiting%20to%20open%20for%20her.%E2%80%9D%20Safeena%20continues%2C%20%E2%80%9CThat%E2%80%99s%20what%20we%E2%80%99re%20working%20towards.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20most%20girls%20in%20India%2C%20educational%20equity%20is%20a%20mirage%3B%20there%2C%20but%20out%20of%20reach.%20And%20through%20its%20projects%2C%20Educate%20Girls%20wants%20to%20challenge%20this.%20It%20wants%20to%20anchor%20equity%20into%20the%20Indian%20academic%20framework%2C%20with%20a%20key%20focus%20on%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F283914%2Fgirls-education-drop-out-educate-girls-pratham-foundation%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emobilising%20communities%20for%20girls%E2%80%99%20education%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20rural%20and%20educationally%20marginalised%20areas.%20The%20NGO%E2%80%99s%20programmes%2C%20aligned%20with%20the%20%E2%80%98Right%20to%20Education%20Act%E2%80%99%2C%20leverage%20the%20Government%E2%80%99s%20existing%20investment%20in%20schools%20and%20engage%20with%20a%20huge%20base%20of%20community%20volunteers%2C%20helping%20to%20identify%2C%20enrol%2C%20and%20retain%20out-of-school%20girls%20and%20improve%20foundational%20skills%20in%20literacy%20and%20numeracy%20for%20all%20children%20(both%20girls%20and%20boys).%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20cases%20where%20formal%20schooling%20isn%E2%80%99t%20an%20option%2C%20Educate%20Girls%20provides%20a%20second-chance%20programme%20to%20help%20girls%20complete%20their%20secondary%20education.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20success%20is%20two-pronged.%20The%20impact%20on%20the%20ground%20exhibits%20two%20million%20out-of-school%20girls%20who%20have%20been%20introduced%20to%20school%2C%20and%20over%2030%2C000%20girls%20and%20women%20who%20have%20gotten%20%E2%80%9Ca%20second%20chance%E2%80%9D%20to%20dream%20by%20being%20reintroduced%20into%20the%20education%20system.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeyond%20data%2C%20Safeena%E2%80%99s%20repository%20of%20success%20stories%20underscores%20the%20impact%20of%20their%20work.%E2%80%9CWhen%20I%20was%20in%20Rajasthan%2C%20a%20young%20girl%20came%20up%20to%20me%20and%20asked%20if%20I%20remembered%20her.%20She%20was%20enrolled%20in%20school%20when%20she%20was%20in%20Class%203.%20She%E2%80%99d%20now%20gone%20on%20to%20become%20the%20%3Cem%3Esarpanch%20%3C%2Fem%3Eof%20her%20village%20and%20shared%20that%20she%20reserved%20a%20significant%20portion%20of%20the%20village%20budget%20for%20girls%E2%80%99%20education.%E2%80%9D%20This%20is%20one%20of%20Safeena%E2%80%99s%20favourite%20stories%20to%20share.%20It%E2%80%99s%20grounded%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F347460%2Fdaily-wager-doctor-builds-school-utkal-gaurav-intern