3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EAppreciating%20nature%20%26amp%3B%20taking%20quality%C2%A0time%20together%20is%20also%20parenting%3B%20Photo%20courtesy%20Pooja%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESwaati%20points%20to%20the%20%E2%80%9Cother-ing%E2%80%9D%20in%20our%20culture.%20%E2%80%9CWe%E2%80%99re%20so%20obsessed%20with%20the%20brain%20of%20the%20neurodivergent%E2%80%A6%20it%E2%80%99s%20in%20these%20binaries%2C%20how%20the%20brain%20is%20failing%2C%20not%20doing%20what%20it%E2%80%99s%20supposed%20to%2C%20or%20how%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20genius%20brain%20%E2%80%94%20%3Cem%3ECPU%20hai%2C%20AI%20hai%3C%2Fem%3E%20(It%E2%80%99s%20like%20saying%20the%20brain%20is%20a%20CPU%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20AI).%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20doing%20so%2C%20she%20says%2C%20we%20lose%20the%20holistic%20view%20%E2%80%94%20the%20human%20view.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20look%20at%20the%20emotions%20of%20the%20child%2C%20the%20humanity%2C%20make%20those%20human%20connections%2C%20then%20how%20will%20anything%20get%20better%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKrishna%2C%20a%20Chennai-based%20special%20educator%2C%20inclusion%20practitioner%2C%20and%20assistive%20technology%20consultant%2C%20offers%20a%20fitting%20analogy%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20design%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3Esari%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20so%20diverse%2C%20accessible.%20The%20same%20%3Cem%3Esari%3C%2Fem%3E%20can%20be%20worn%20by%20people%20of%20multiple%20sizes%20and%20shapes.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20point%3A%20a%20common%20framework%20that%20adapts%20to%20individual%20needs.%20The%20Universal%20Design%20of%20Learning%20(UDL)%2C%20which%20Krishna%20cites%2C%20applies%20this%20principle%20to%20education.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPriya%2C%20a%20Mumbai-based%20single%20parent%2C%20writer%2C%20and%20actor%2C%20translates%20this%20into%20her%20parenting.%20She%20shares%20a%20pandemic%20anecdote%20about%20her%20father%20teaching%20her%20son%20Math%20over%20video%20calls.%20Initially%20focused%20on%20discipline%2C%20the%20grandfather%20scolded%20the%20boy%20for%20slouching%20%E2%80%94%20until%20encouraged%20to%20check%20for%20understanding%20instead.%20He%20then%20realised%20the%20child%20had%20grasped%20everything%20despite%20his%20posture.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThat%E2%80%99s%20when%20I%20told%20my%20dad%2C%20%E2%80%98Sitting%20straight%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20necessarily%20mean%20paying%20attention.%20In%20fact%2C%20if%20he%20was%20sitting%20straight%2C%20he%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20be%20able%20to%20learn.%E2%80%99%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%2015%2C%20Priya%E2%80%99s%20son%20Arhant%20learns%20best%20through%20theatre.%20%E2%80%9CHe%20can%20watch%20plays%20with%20very%20complex%20themes%20and%20learn%20from%20them.%E2%80%9D%20Accepting%20that%20children%20learn%20in%20different%20ways%20and%20customising%20the%20experience%20accordingly%20can%20be%20deeply%20fulfilling%2C%20even%20if%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20the%20norm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Priya%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20actually%20feel%20this%20is%20a%20more%20authentic%20life%20because%20you%20don%E2%80%99t%20fall%20into%20all%20the%20usual%20traps%20that%20neurotypical%20folks%20do.%E2%80%9D%20Her%20son%20has%20opted%20out%20of%20the%20traditional%20schooling%20system%2C%20focusing%20on%20the%20guitar%2C%20logical%20reasoning%2C%20and%20Kalari.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20good%20parenting%20is%20truly%20child-led%2C%20then%20this%20off-the-beaten-track%20approach%20might%20be%20one%20of%20its%20purest%20forms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EThe%20hidden%20weight%20parents%20carry%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20path%20is%20far%20from%20rosy.%20There%20is%20harsh%20family%20judgment%20and%20biting%20social%20censure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAditi%2C%20CEO%20of%20Much%20Much%20Spectrum%20%E2%80%94%20a%20Mumbai-based%20storytelling%20studio%20focused%20on%20intersectional%20narratives%20around%20mental%20health%2C%20disability%2C%20and%20neurodivergence%20%E2%80%94%20speaks%20of%20the%20stigma%20and%20shame%20parents%20face%20if%20their%20child%20is%20marked%20as%20different.%20%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20recognised%20as%20%3Cem%3Etumhare%20pichle%20janam%20ke%20paap%3C%2Fem%3E%20(the%20sins%20from%20your%20past%20life)%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESwaati%20shares%20that%20half%20her%20role%20as%20a%20parent%20is%20myth-busting.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20a%20perception%20that%20these%20children%20are%20violent%2C%20that%20they%20have%20no%20control%E2%80%A6%20they%20even%20use%20the%20word%20%3Cem%3Epaagal%20%3C%2Fem%3E(mad).%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPriya%20adds%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Indian%20family%20mindset%20means%20that%20anything%20that%20makes%20it%20less%20strong%2C%20we%20mask%20it%2C%20because%20as%20a%20unit%2C%20we%20need%20to%20hide%20the%20weakest%20link%2C%20right%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20ingrained%20mindset%2C%20experts%20say%2C%20is%20why%20the%20system%20fails%20children%20%E2%80%94%20its%20cracks%20showing%20up%20in%20every%20sphere%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F325345%2Fdelhi-tarini-malhotra-started-nai-subah-foundation-ngo-for-neurodivergent-community-get-jobs%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eneurodivergent%20child%E2%80%99s%20life%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20from%20education%20and%20healthcare%20to%20insurance%20and%20justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-quote%20wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EShreya%20Munoth%2C%20Advocate-on-Record%20at%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20Partner%20at%20Chakravorty%20Samson%20%26amp%3B%20Munoth%2C%20tells%20me%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20not%20a%20regulated%20system%2C%20and%20the%20implementation%20is%20uneven.%E2%80%9D%20She%20highlights%20major%20gaps%20in%20enforcing%20the%20Rights%20of%20Persons%20with%20Disabilities%20(RPWD)%20Act%2C%20especially%20for%20autism.%20While%20the%202016%20amendment%20expanded%20the%20list%20of%20reco