yothi-chitra-paul%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esomething%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20fully%20understand%20yet%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20know%20my%20child%20is%20not%20the%20sum%20of%20these%20points.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F417379%2Fmugdha-kalra-shares-parenting-methods-raising-autistic-child-world-autism-awareness-day%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChildren%20are%20meant%20to%20be%20loved%20and%20cared%20for%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20not%20analysed%2C%20right%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPriya%20treats%20the%20assessment%20as%20%E2%80%9Csomething%20to%20go%20back%20to%20when%20needed.%E2%80%9D%20Even%20before%20the%20formal%20report%2C%20she%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20was%2085%25%20on%20the%20right%20track%20with%20my%20own%20research%20into%20ADHD.%20The%20assessment%20helped%20with%20future%20course-correction%20and%20to%20ideate%20on%20what%20else%20can%20be%20done%20to%20support%20him.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20perspective%20runs%20through%20Shelja%E2%80%99s%20professional%20work%20as%20well.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20can%E2%80%99t%20make%20it%20the%20central%2C%20defining%20narrative%20of%20our%20lives%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20therapies%20are%20important%20but%20don%E2%80%99t%20make%20them%20central%20to%20the%20experience%20of%20your%20parenting.%20We%E2%80%99re%20creating%20more%20storms%20in%20our%20lives%20and%20in%20our%20children%E2%80%99s%20lives%20too.%20I%20tell%20the%20parents%20that%20we%20just%20need%20to%20provide%20the%20soil%20to%20our%20children%20%E2%80%94%20just%20focus%20on%20your%20relationship%20with%20the%20child%2C%20connect%20with%20the%20child%2C%20play.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20champions%20the%20%E2%80%9Cplayfulness%20quotient%E2%80%9D%20or%20PQ%2C%20as%20she%20calls%20it.%20%E2%80%9CForget%20about%20IQ%2C%20EQ%2C%20focus%20on%20PQ!%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C